To differentiate  

 f(x) = 2^{4x} + 4x^{2}

use the fact that d/dx [a^{u(x)}] = a^{u(x)}·ln(a)·u′(x).

1. Derivative of 2^{4x}  
   u(x)=4x ⇒ u′(x)=4  
   d/dx[2^{4x}] = 2^{4x} · ln 2 · 4 = 4 ln 2 · 2^{4x}

2. Derivative of 4x²  
   d/dx[4x²] = 8x

Combine the results:

 f′(x) = 4 ln 2 · 2^{4x} + 8x.
